lass="_ _9"></span>______________________</div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 ybbe ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">_________________________<span class="_ _4"></span>___<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>______________________</div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y86d ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">_________________________<span class="_ _4"></span>___<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>______________________</div><div class="t m0 x58 h36 ybbf ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws110">Sin had broken the relationship between God and humanity. God </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 ybc0 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsec">sent the couple away from His presence for their own protection. </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 ybc1 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Humans could no longer see God’s face and live. </div><div class="t m0 x58 h36 ybc2 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws29">The Lord, though, of His own initiative, brought in the plan of sal<span class="ws5">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 ybc3 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws26">vation, through which the broken relationship could be healed, even </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 ybc4 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">at a terrible cost to Himself. </div><div class="t m15 x3b h32 ybc5 ff14 fs19 fc6 sc0 ls2 ws5">Read</div><div class="t m0 x5b h34 ybc5 ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws8e"> John 14:1–3 and Revelation 22:3–5. What promise did Jesus </div><div class="t m0 x45 h34 ybc6 ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws104">extend to His disciples just before He went to the cross, and what </div><div class="t m0 x45 h34 ybc7 ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">will be the result?</div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y88d ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">_________________________<span class="_ _4"></span>___<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>__<span class="_ _9"></span>_____________